Additionally, the paper mentions machine learning techniques, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of Bloom filters in databases, which suggests that it may belong to the category of database systems (cs.DB). Furthermore, the paper proposes a method for optimizing the performance of learned Bloom filters, which suggests that it may belong to the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of Bloom filters, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of cryptography (cs.CR).
